# Cogniplane Core — root .env.example
#
# This is a placeholder. Cogniplane Core is a pnpm monorepo: the actual
# configuration lives in per-app .env files.
#
# Quickstart:
#   cp apps/backend/.env.example apps/backend/.env
#   cp apps/frontend/.env.example apps/frontend/.env.local
#
# See apps/backend/.env.example for the backend env-var reference, including:
#   - DATABASE_URL / MIGRATION_DATABASE_URL
#   - AUTH_MODE (dev-headers vs. workos)
#   - JWT_SECRET / DATA_ENCRYPTION_SECRET (production: 32+ random bytes each)
#   - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (optional; enables the Claude runtime — paid Anthropic
#     console key required, consumer Free/Pro/Max subscriptions are NOT
#     supported by the Agent SDK; governed by https://www.anthropic.com/legal/commercial-terms)
#   - OPENAI_API_KEY (optional; enables the Codex runtime when no per-tenant key is set)
#   - REDIS_URL, ARTIFACT_BUCKET_*, E2B_API_KEY, etc.
#   - PII_RETENTION_KEK (required only when any tenant uses
#     `rawRetention='reversible_encrypted'`; 32 bytes hex, e.g.
#     `openssl rand -hex 32`)
#
# In production deployments, prefer saving model-provider keys per-tenant in
# admin → org settings (encrypted at rest, scopable per tenant) instead of in
# env vars. The runtime resolves keys as: tenant key → env fallback → null.
#
# See docs/getting-started.md and docs/self-hosting.md for full configuration.
